other_tests.findings: Afib with rate 107, ST depressions in V3-V5.
Poorly differentiated carcinoma with some morphologic and immunohistochemical features consistent with squamous cell carcinoma.
Multiple hypoenhancing liver metastases, some larger than prior study. New small bilateral pleural effusions. Small pericardial effusion minimally increased.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Largest mass in segment VII of the liver grew from 35 x 23 mm to 42 x 29 mm; mass in segment V grew from 44 x 39 mm to 47 x 46 mm.
